really, if you

00:10:52.300 --> 00:10:54.230
look at-- if you think
about who are some

00:10:54.230 --> 00:10:57.516
of the most nonviolent and
peaceful people on the planet,

00:10:57.516 --> 00:10:59.140
you say, well, you
know, Buddhist monks

00:10:59.140 --> 00:10:59.960
or Shaolin monks.

00:10:59.960 --> 00:11:01.210
I'm like, exactly.

00:11:01.210 --> 00:11:04.790
And they train their whole
life in blades, in punching,

00:11:04.790 --> 00:11:08.150
in kicking, in throwing
stars and all these weapons.

00:11:08.150 --> 00:11:11.989
And it's because they have
confronted all of these fears

00:11:11.989 --> 00:11:14.280
and all of these concerns
about violence and everything

00:11:14.280 --> 00:11:16.340
else that they're
completely at peace.

00:11:16.340 --> 00:11:18.084
And so people don't
understand that.

00:11:18.084 --> 00:11:19.500
A lot of the
violence that happens

00:11:19.500 --> 00:11:21.110
is because these kids
are stressed out.

00:11:21.110 --> 00:11:22.651
They don't have any
physical outlets.

00:11:22.651 --> 00:11:28.451
They have no way and no filter
of how to assess and understand

00:11:28.451 --> 00:11:29.450
what's really happening.

00:11:29.450 --> 00:11:30.890
And that's why they lash out.

00:11:30.890 --> 00:11:36.000
And so that's why Brazilian
jiu-jitsu is what we teach.

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:37.630
And so this is at
one of the schools

00:11:37.630 --> 00:11:40.260
here in the Bay, down
in East Side San Jose.

00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:42.300
And it was really crazy,
because this school,

00:11:42.300 --> 00:11:46.260
