seen the movie "Fresh."

00:18:53.110 --> 00:18:59.350
it's a movie from the '80s about
this kid whose older sister is

00:18:59.350 --> 00:19:01.600
being pimped out by
this heroin dealer,

00:19:01.600 --> 00:19:04.160
but his father, who's
played by Samuel Jackson,

00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:05.870
is a street hustler
who plays chess.

00:19:05.870 --> 00:19:08.720
And so the more that the kid
plays chess with his father,

00:19:08.720 --> 00:19:12.430
he figures out how he
can get his sister away

00:19:12.430 --> 00:19:13.480
from the drug dealer.

00:19:13.480 --> 00:19:15.340
And so it's a great film.

00:19:15.340 --> 00:19:17.590
And then the movie like
"Searching for Bobby Fischer,"

00:19:17.590 --> 00:19:20.930
you know, it's about Josh
Waitzkin, and so, you know,

00:19:20.930 --> 00:19:27.070
Josh's entry into chess
is playing in the streets.

00:19:27.070 --> 00:19:29.090
And then he gets a
classical teacher,

00:19:29.090 --> 00:19:31.400
and there's kind of like
this philosophical breakdown,

00:19:31.400 --> 00:19:33.780
and he ends up going back
to the street hustler

00:19:33.780 --> 00:19:35.495
to help him get
his game back up.

00:19:35.495 --> 00:19:36.870
And ironically,
in his real life,

00:19:36.870 --> 00:19:38.360
he ends up quitting
chess and then going on

00:19:38.360 --> 00:19:40.230
to get a black belt in
Brazilian jiu-jitsu,

00:19:40.230 --> 00:19:44.960
and he's a really
good dude at that.

00:19:44.960 --> 00:19:49.040
So I tell the kids, you know,
Jay-Z, Will Smith, these guys

00:19:49.040 --> 00:19:51.241
are not successes by accident,
you know what I mean?

00:19:51.241 --> 00:19:52.490
They think about what they do.

00:19:52.490 --> 00:19:53.448
They plan what they do.

00:19:53.448 --> 00:19:56.147
And you need these
tools to be successful,

00:19:56.147 --> 00:19:58.230
and that any success that
you get that you haven't

00:19:58.230 --> 00:20:00.270
planned for, you lose it.

00:20:00.270 --> 00:20:02.270
You see people all the
time who win the lottery.

00:20:02.270 --> 00:20:04.436
In three years they're broke
and back in the trailer

00:20:04.436 --> 00:20:06.990
home or whatever, because they
don't know what they're doing.

00:20:06.990 --> 00:20:08.490
They didn't plan
to have that money.

00:20:08.490 --> 00:20:10.281
And so you should make
plans to have money.

00:20:10.281 --> 00:20:12.150
You should make plans
to enhance your wisdom

00:20:12.150 --> 00:20:14.358
and figure out where you're
going to be down the line

00:20:14.358 --> 00:20:16.110
and how to quantify
it and qualify it.

00:20:16.110 --> 00:20:18.120
And so that's what's in my book.

00:20:18.120 --> 00:20:19.750
In the back they
have these 12 filters

00:20:19.750 --> 00:20:23.980
about long- and short-term
goal planning and other things.

